# Liquid Glass UI (`liquid_glass_widgets`)

**Exclusive UI kit** for the navigation chrome retheme. Package: [sdegenaar/liquid_glass_widgets](https://github.com/sdegenaar/liquid_glass_widgets) (pub: `liquid_glass_widgets`).

Requires **Flutter ≥ 3.41** (project on 3.44+). Query **Context7** before guessing widget APIs.

**Do not use `liquid_glass_easy`.** Its metaball shaders fail SkSL compilation on Linux desktop (Skia default renderer). All glass chrome uses `liquid_glass_widgets` only — `AdaptiveGlass`, `GlassContainer`, `GlassScaffold`, etc.

## Linux / Skia compatibility

| Surface | Linux desktop (Skia) |
|---------|----------------------|
| App bars, tab bars, side rail shell | `GlassQuality.standard` — lightweight shader path |
| Side nav chrome | `GlassContainer` + `embyChromeGlassSettings()` |
| Premium shaders | Impeller-only — auto-capped by `adaptiveQuality` |

Project wires glass via `LiquidGlassWidgets.wrap()` + `loadEmbyGlassAdaptiveConfig()` in `main.dart`. See `lib/theme/emby_glass_theme.dart`.

## Vitreous refraction pipeline (Impeller / Vulkan)

Custom shader path in `lib/graphics/` — **requires Impeller** (`flutter run -d linux --enable-impeller`).

| Component | Role |
|-----------|------|
| `VitreousGlassShader` | Loads `shaders/vitreous_glass.frag`, binds `ui.Image` sampler |
| `RefractionController` | `RepaintBoundary.toImage(Sync)` snapshot management |
| `VitreousGlassHost` | Wraps opaque main content for backdrop capture |
| `VitreousGlassSurface` | Shader-only chrome layer (side rail) |
| `liquid_glass_widgets` | Structural chrome when Impeller off or for tab bars |

Do **not** use `BackdropFilter` for refraction on Linux. Falls back to `GlassContainer` when Impeller unavailable.

## Setup (app root — once)

```dart
void main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  await LiquidGlassWidgets.initialize();
  final glassAdaptiveConfig = await loadEmbyGlassAdaptiveConfig();

  runApp(embyGlassWrapApp(
    adaptiveConfig: glassAdaptiveConfig,
    child: const EmbyPlayerApp(),
  ));
}
```

**Persist adaptive quality** across cold starts (recommended for Linux/Android mid-range):

```dart
// Load saved GlassQuality from SharedPreferences → adaptiveConfig.initialQuality
// onQualityChanged → persist quality name — see package README "Eliminating repeat warmup jank"
```

Accessibility (Reduce Motion / Reduce Transparency) is **automatic** — do not disable unless user-facing setting.

## Glass vs content — non-negotiable

Glass is **navigation and control chrome only**. Content stays **opaque** — same rule as iOS 26.

| ✅ Glass | ❌ Opaque (standard Material/Cupertino) |
|----------|----------------------------------------|
| App bars, tab bars, bottom bars, toolbars | `MediaCard`, library grids, episode tiles |
| Side nav **chrome** (floating rail shell) | Poster/backdrop art, hero imagery |
| Sheets, dialogs, menus, popovers, toasts | Settings **row content** (use list tiles) |
| FABs, segmented controls, search bars | **Video player** surface and controls stack |
| `GlassSwitch`, `GlassSlider`, `GlassChip` in toolbars | Full-screen browse backgrounds |

```
┌──────────────────────────┐
│   GlassAppBar (glass)    │  ← chrome
├──────────────────────────┤
│   Opaque content         │  ← ListView, MediaCard, grids
│   (MonoTokens / Theme)   │
├──────────────────────────┤
│  GlassBottomBar (glass)  │  ← chrome
└──────────────────────────┘
```

**Settings:** `GlassScaffold` + `GlassAppBar` for chrome; **opaque** `ListTile` / `CupertinoListTile` rows in body. Optional: `GlassGroupedSection` for grouped glass-styled sections only when design calls for it — not every row.

## Primary pattern: `GlassScaffold`

Default for **all standard screens** (libraries, settings, hub, auth shell). Replaces `Scaffold` + manual transparent background + `FocusedScrollScaffold` chrome.

```dart
GlassScaffold(
  background: _appBackdrop(context), // fanart gradient, blurred library art, or themed wallpaper
  statusBarStyle: GlassStatusBarStyle.auto,
  contentAwareBrightness: true,
  appBar: GlassAppBar(title: Text(t.libraries.title)),
  bottomBar: GlassTabBar.bottom(/* main tabs */),
  body: CustomScrollView(slivers: [/* opaque content slivers */]),
)
```

| Need | Widget |
|------|--------|
| Screen with app bar / tab bar | **`GlassScaffold`** or **`EmbyGlassScrollScaffold`** (settings pilot) |
| Side nav shell chrome | **`GlassContainer`** (`embyChromeGlassSettings`) — chrome only |
| Bottom navigation (mobile) | **`GlassTabBar.bottom`** |
| In-page library tabs (mobile) | **`GlassSegmentedControl`** |
| Custom stack layout (main shell + side rail) | **`GlassPage`** + manual `Stack`, or extend shell widget |
| Modal / picker | **`GlassSheet`**, **`GlassModalSheet`**, **`GlassDialog`** |
| Context menu | **`GlassMenu`** + **`GlassMenuItem`** (Liquid Morph engine) |
| Toolbar actions | **`GlassButton`**, **`GlassIconButton`**, **`GlassButtonGroup`** |
| Search | **`GlassSearchBar`** or **`GlassTabBar.searchable()`** |
| Low-level one-off glass panel | **`GlassCard`** / **`GlassContainer`** / **`AdaptiveGlass`** — not the default for whole screens |

Do **not** assemble `GlassPage` + `Scaffold` + `GlassScrollEdgeEffect` + `Stack` manually when `GlassScaffold` covers the case.

## Emby Player screen mapping

| Current surface | Target | Notes |
|-----------------|--------|-------|
| `MainScreen` shell | `GlassScaffold` or `GlassPage` + opaque body | Keep provider/focus logic; swap chrome |
| `SideNavigationRail` | `GlassContainer` sidebar chrome + **opaque** `NavigationRailItem` content | Preserve `DpadNavigator` / focus nodes — glass wraps chrome, not focus target internals |
| `SettingsPage` / `FocusedScrollScaffold` | `EmbyGlassScrollScaffold` + `GlassAppBar` + opaque sliver list | Rows stay Material/Cupertino |
| `MediaCard`, `EpisodeCard`, grids | **No glass** — keep opaque cards | Use `MonoTokens` / `Theme` |
| `video_player` screen | **Opaque** player + optional glass **overlay** controls only | Never glass the video texture |
| `OverlaySheet`, bottom sheets | `GlassModalSheet` / `GlassSheet` | Migrate gradually |
| Dialogs / PIN entry | `GlassDialog` | |
| Auth / profile switch | `GlassScaffold` + opaque form content | |

## Quality & performance (Linux + TV)

| Surface | Quality | Why |
|---------|---------|-----|
| App bar, bottom bar, side rail shell | `standard`; Impeller mobile may promote via `GlassIsolationScope` | Fixed chrome |
| Scrollable lists / grids | **opaque** — no glass cards in list | GPU budget |
| Hero / static feature panel | `premium` on Impeller only; **never** inside scroll views | Shader cost |
| Low-end / many glass elements | `GlassQuality.minimal` for secondary panels | Zero shader in scroll |
| Linux desktop (Skia) | `standard` default; lightweight shader path | Auto-detected |

Enable `adaptiveQuality: true` in `wrap()`; persist settled tier to avoid 3s warmup jank every launch.

**Debug only:** `GlassPerformanceMonitor` via `LiquidGlassWidgets.initialize()` — zero cost in release.

## Theming bridge

- App-wide glass defaults: `LiquidGlassWidgets.wrap(theme: GlassThemeData(...))`.
- Opaque content: keep **`MonoTokens`** / `ThemeExtension` for surfaces, text, radii on cards and lists.
- Override hierarchy (highest wins): widget `settings` → `GlassPage(themeOverride:)` → `wrap(theme:)`.
- Per-subtree: `GlassTheme(data: GlassThemeData.simple(...), child: ...)`.
- Side rail chrome: `embyChromeGlassSettings(context)` in `lib/theme/emby_glass_theme.dart`.

Do not duplicate color hex in glass widgets — use `GlassThemeData` + `GlassGlowColors` for interaction glow on bars.

## TV / D-pad / gamepad

- **Focus system stays** — `lib/focus/`, `FocusableMediaCard`, `DpadNavigator` are unchanged.
- Glass bars must not steal focus from content rail; verify RIGHT/LEFT between sidebar and grid after migration.
- `contentAwareBrightness: true` on `GlassScaffold` when content scrolls under floating bars (hub/library).
- 10-foot targets: prefer `GlassButton` size defaults; test with `GamepadService`.

## Migration rules

1. **Chrome first** — `main.dart` wrap + one pilot screen (`SettingsPage` or library hub).
2. **Extract shared shell** — `EmbyGlassScrollScaffold` wrapping `GlassScaffold` with backdrop + tab bar wiring.
3. **Leave providers/services untouched** — UI-only diff per screen.
4. **Delete replaced scaffolds** only after all call sites migrate (`FocusedScrollScaffold`, duplicate app bars).
5. Reference package examples: `example/lib/demos/nav_bar_patterns_demo.dart`, `content_aware_brightness_demo.dart`, Apple News demo (article tiles = opaque).

## Widget catalog (quick reference)

**Surfaces:** `GlassScaffold`, `GlassAppBar`, `GlassTabBar`, `GlassToolbar`, `GlassPage`  
**Interactive:** `GlassButton`, `GlassIconButton`, `GlassSegmentedControl`, `GlassSwitch`, `GlassSlider`, `GlassChip`  
**Input:** `GlassTextField`, `GlassSearchBar`, `GlassPicker`  
**Overlays:** `GlassDialog`, `GlassSheet`, `GlassModalSheet`, `GlassMenu`, `showGlassActionSheet`  
**Containers (sparingly):** `GlassCard`, `GlassGroupedSection`, `GlassListTile`, `GlassContainer`, `AdaptiveGlass` — not for media grids

## Forbidden

- **`liquid_glass_easy`** — metaball shaders break Linux Skia; never add to pubspec
- `GlassCard` / `GlassContainer` wrapping **`MediaCard`** or poster grids
- Glass on **`Player` / video texture** / MPV overlay background
- Raw `Scaffold` with transparent background on new screens — use `GlassScaffold`
- `GlassQuality.premium` inside `ListView` / `CustomScrollView` slivers
- Removing accessibility fallbacks (`respectSystemAccessibility: false`) without product approval
- New Material `AppBar` / `NavigationBar` on migrated screens — use glass equivalents
- Hardcoded strings — still use slang `t.*`

